Poster for the China National Film Museum's Italian movie season Photo: Courtesy of the Beijing New Film AssociationA series of Italian movies will be screened in Beijing as part of the China National Film Museum's international screening season, according to a press conference hosted by the museum and the Beijing New Film Association on Tuesday.   A total of five films will be screened until Sunday, including A Tuscan Heaven (2016), Sicilian Ghost Story (2017) and The Man with the Magic Box (2017). After the Italian event, the China National Film Museum and Beijing New Film Association plan to screen movies from five countries including Hungary, Poland and Bulgaria. 
